To run:
Start up.
Clear the screen.
Draw some dots on the left side of the screen.
Draw some stars on the right side of the screen.
Write the total object count then " objects" at the bottom of the screen.
Refresh the screen.
Wait for the escape key.
Shut down.

To draw some dots on the left side of the screen:
Pick a count between 1 and 5.
Add the count to the total object count.
Loop.
Pick a spot on the left side of the screen.
Draw a dot 1/2 inch wide on the spot with the green pen.
Subtract 1 from the count.
If the count is greater than 0, repeat.

To draw some stars on the right side of the screen:
Pick a count between 1 and 5.
Add the count to the total object count.
Loop.
Pick a spot on the right side of the screen.
Draw a star 1/2 inch wide on the spot with the gold pen.
Subtract 1 from the count.
If the count is greater than 0, repeat.